EnergySense is a project focused on accurate short-term load forecasting and anomaly detection for commercial and residential buildings. The goal is to enable efficient energy management, integrate renewable energy sources, and reduce reliance on fossil fuels by leveraging time-series forecasting and data analysis techniques.

Sample Datasets:

- Building Energy Dataset (UCI): https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Building+Energy
- ASHRAE Energy Prediction Dataset (Kaggle): https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/ashrae-energy-prediction/data
- Open Power System Data: https://data.open-power-system-data.org/

Reference Resources

- Introduction to Time Series Forecasting: https://otexts.com/fpp3/
- PyTorch Forecasting Documentation: https://pytorch-forecasting.readthedocs.io/
- Time Series Foundation Models (TSFMs) Paper: https://arxiv.org/abs/2303.12345
